Description:
Calling All First Home Buyers and Investors.
With easy access to the CBD, local shops, schools and public transport this location is sure to appeal. Perfect for those wanting to enter the real estate market or an addition to your rental portfolio do not miss this opportunity. Set on 779m2 with the potential to further enhance, extend, renovate, or develop (STCA) this really is a fantastic opportunity.
Three bedrooms, two with BIRs are complimented by a neat bathroom with shower, bath and separate toilet.
The lounge room with plenty of natural light flows through to the kitchen/dining area. The kitchen with upright stove/gas cooktop plenty of bench space and oversized pantry is very practical.
Heating and cooling is accounted for with a split system, Arrow wood heater, gas upright heater and ceiling fan in the master bedroom
Comprising of oversized SLUG, double carport with further off street parking for 3 cars.
Minutes from local schools, Newcomb Shopping Centre, Splashdown Aquatic Centre and Geelong CBD. This is an easy investment or ideal property to enter Geelong's growing market.

Address: 6A St James Street St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
Low Maintenance Living
Presented in immaculate condition, this easy-care home showcases expansive open-plan living and an enviable indoor-outdoor lifestyle. Gorgeous floors and an abundance of windows ensure the home feels bright and inviting and will put you at ease from the moment you step through the front door. There are three spacious bedrooms with built in robes and master complete with a large walk in robe and full ensuite. Overlooking the dining and living zone is the stylish kitchen finished with stainless steel appliances, a breakfast bar, ample storage and a dishwasher. At the heart of the home is the sprawling open plan living and dining area combing indoor and outdoor living perfect for hosting family and friends. A central bathroom with a separate bath and shower, laundry with plenty of storage and single garage with internal access and drive-through roller door complete the floorplan. Extra features include ducted heating throughout, remote-controlled air-conditioning, CCTV cameras and a garden shed. Outside the gardens and backyard are all low maintenance making it the perfect downsizer, first home or set-and-forget investment. Located just 6 minutes from the Geelong CBD and with public transport, local shops and schools all nearby you won't for anything.
Due Diligence checklist are available at www.consumer.vic.gov.au/duediligencechecklist

Description:
Premier Location in East Geelong
This charming weatherboard home located in one of East Geelong's premier streets is immaculate in its presentation and offers a lifestyle of convenience very few properties can match.
Behind the stunning facade this is a home where you will want for nothing, featuring 3 bedrooms with the light-filled master featuring a beautiful bay window and ensuite, whilst the remaining 2 bedrooms have BIRs. The updated kitchen adds a modern touch to this character filled home, stone bench tops, a stainless steel 900ml oven and tiled splash-back create a chef's quality kitchen, combined with the large butler's pantry this space is maximised to its full potential.
The kitchen overlooks the dining and living area which opens up to the large deck, a space that will make entertaining a breeze, easily big enough to host the family for Christmas dinner!
If that's not enough there is also a fully self contained bungalow at the rear of the property, with a full bathroom, split system heating and cooling making it ideal as a guest room or for a family member.
The home is complete with extras such as a large remote DLUG with workshop space, split system heating and cooling, original Baltic Pine flooring and has been beautifully maintained.
Located just a short walk from Garden Street shops & cafes, hospitals, Geelong CBD, the Eastern Gardens and Waterfront.
This property will be sure to tick all the boxes so an inspection here is a must!
Terms: 10% deposit, 90 Day settlement. For alternative arrangements please discuss with the agent.

Description:
WAREHOUSE STYLE LIVING IN PRIME EAST GEELONG POCKET
This spacious and newly updated 2 bed,1 bath, large living townhouse in a prime pocket of East Geelong would suit an array of buyers and is one to inspect.
Set in a group of only 4, this 2 storey property comprises of an open plan design featuring large living space downstairs, equipped with built in custom floating cabinetry, a newly updated kitchen offering quality SS appliances, 4 burner gas cooking, Bosch dishwasher and push-to-open kitchen draws plus wonderful central island bench.
The dining space located directly off the kitchen easily accommodates up to 8 and is perfect for entertaining friends.
Towards the rear of the home you will find a handy laundry space and toilet.
Upstairs you will find a central bathroom with modern shower over bath, a 2nd toilet and vanity storage.
The 2 bedrooms are a spacious 6m x 3m and offer BIR, block-out blinds and wonderful large double glazed windows offering an abundance of natural light to flood in.
Outside you will find a secure front and back deck ideal to soak up the sun and relax.
This quality investment, first home or ideal downsizer is conveniently located close to South Geelong train station, local parks and 5 mins walk to Eastern Beach Geelong.

Off the living room you will find the well-equipped Kitchen, tastefully updated with Caesar stone benchtops, stainless steel European appliances, stylish subway tiled splash back and quality fittings.
Opening the hardwood barndoor down the hall you will find 3 good sized bedrooms, the master offering large BIR's and ceiling fan, the 2nd with ceiling fan and a leafy front garden outlook. The 3rd bedroom is located at the rear of the home and would make for an ideal study or nursery. The central bathroom has been beautifully updated with matching subway tiles, modern vanity, and stylish bath and shower equipped with rain head. You will also find an updated laundry also with subway tiles and a second separate toilet. Outside you will find a cottage front garden, garden shed and good-sized rear yard, perfect for children or your 4-legged friend, plus a single lock up garage with side access with no clearance restrictions, accommodating up to 2-3 cars. This great corner property is ideally located a short drive to local shopping centers, close proximity to schools and sorting facilities, only minutes' walk to "The Hive" Early Learning Centre, less than 3km from Geelong CBD and 15 minutes' drive to the Bellarine coastline.

Description:
CALLING INVESTORS, FHB or TRADIE NEEDING AMPLE PARKING
This solid 1960's BV 3 bedroom, 1 bathroom, 1 large living and DLUG set on a generous 575 m2 block, would suit a FHB couple, property flipper, Tradie, with secure gates and ample parking, a savvy investor with a potential rent pw of $340 approx
Tucked away in a quiet street and behind a leafy established front garden this property comprises of spacious front lounge room equipped with Vulcan gas heater, and Panasonic air-con box for all year round comfort.
The informal meals area sits perfectly next to the updated kitchen and easily accommodates up to 6+. The kitchen has tasteful hardwood cabinetry, Westinghouse 4 burner gas cooktop and electric oven.
Off the hallway you will find 2 bedrooms with BIR, a central bathroom featuring a corner shower, vanity and separate toilet.
Stepping down the hallway you will find a large study with views onto the rear of the property and spa area. At the rear of the home you will also find a huge master bedroom equipped with triple BIR and extra toilet.
Outside you will find a large, powered DLUG and a long driveway easily accommodating additional cars. This property also offers established front and back gardens for your children to enjoy, four legged friend or avid green thumb.
This property is ideally located in growing Thomson and in a quiet street, close to nearby shops, sporting grounds and 5 minutes drive to Geelong CBD.

Description:
Entry Level Buying At Its Very Best.
Forget the fixer upper and land banker; This one is the perfect entry level property for the genuine first home buyer, investor or long term developer. Set on an imposing allotment of approximately 710 square metres this beautifully presented 3 bedroom weatherboard home needs nothing more to make it complete other than a house full of furniture.
Updated with style the home is comprised of 3 spacious bedrooms, central living area with reverse cycle heating and cooling unit, adjoining dining area off the simple yet modern kitchen and updated bathroom featuring stylish tiling and quality fixtures.
Notable extras include new carpet and blinds and a fresh coat of paint right throughout, Impressive vinyl flooring in the kitchen and meals area and the entire exterior of the home has been given a once over to give the new buyer that new home feel when they move in.
Walking out to the massive rear yard is a sight to behold with a blank canvas waiting for the lucky purchaser to make their own and plenty of space for the kids to play in privacy or the budding developer will be licking their lips at the opportunity that presents (STCA). Theres ample car accommodation available with a long driveway leading down to a single car lock up garage with workshop space and for those that require public transport theres bus routes nearby that will take you to all that Geelong has to offer in only minutes. There are schools, 2 shopping centres, Splashdown and sporting facilities all within a short distance and once youre on the Bellarine Highway there is a world of fun available with wineries, Adventure Park and Daniels donuts in Portarlington all a nice Sunday drive away.
Dont delay as properties in this price range are as rare as hens teeth, make the time to inspect today and prepare to be impressed.
